Frankly, I expected more for the price I paid. I spent $35 for 10 wings x 2, large fries and small coleslaw side order. I got “boneless wings” which appeared to be diced chicken tenders. Some of the pieces were impossible to chew, disgustingly rubber-tasting. Either cheap, or not fresh. Even though I got a total of 12 pieces, instead of 10, I prefer quality, not quantity.  The staff was nice and friendly, but I wouldn’t recommend the food from this place.
Food there is pretty hot, and a nice variety. Cut-to-the-chase good chicken.
Quick service and good wings. They have a bunch of different sauces. I tried the mango habanero and it had a nice kick.
The delivery time wasn’t bad and the delivery man was nice. But the food was mediocre. The wings were dry, the tenders were dry, the fries were hard, and nothing was seasoned well. Do better.

We ordered via a third-party app and chose no-contact delivery. The delivery guy arrived within the given time range and was wearing a mask (big thanks!). They got all our orders right and the food itself hit the spot.

Absolutely putrid, a complete rip-off.  Took almost 2 hours for an Uber Eats order, all of which was spent by the driver waiting to receive the food. Just didn’t deliver the food and when I called the next day, asking if they’d deliver it now that they are actually open, they said deal with grubhub and hung up on me. To close early, see that someone ordered when you were supposed to be open, and still refuse to deliver or offer free food as an apology? Don’t give them a cent.

I clearly and repeatedly told the guy that I wanted boneless wings. And when I took my order back home, I open it and find regular bone-in wings. I really hate having bones in any meat I order and so I couldn’t eat it. It was super hard and not well seasoned according to my mom who ate it instead of me. Also there was no ranch dip included either. They need to start listening to what their customers want, I don’t get how hard it is to understand English. I feel like this is rip off of the Atomic wings which is in Jamaica, which serves great food btw. Save yourself the trouble, skip this location. Not worth wasting your money here.

Being a Buffalonian, I am always on the hunt for wings that can match up to what we have upstate and Atomic Wings didn't disappoint. After a busy day exploring Brooklyn, some friends and I went to test out what Atomic Wings had to offer and their variety of sauces and quality of wings were outstanding! Will definitely be recommending Atomic Wings to any of my friends who find themselves in Brooklyn! Will need to go back and try what the rest of the menu has to offer.

Absolutely, without a doubt love this place. Never once had a bad experience with customer service, cleanliness of the place or the quality of food. Always glad I chose this place to dine in/out. Will highly recommend you check it out. The wings are 100% worth the money you will drop on them alone for a single order. The  choices of sauces ranging from mild to hot you can't go wrong. They even have a unique BBQ sauce. I always go for the BBQ mixed well done with extra sauce ON the wings. Never, not once, left uhappy. They do offer plenty of other menu items that ads worth trying.

Food here is EXCELLENT!!! Hands down, best wings. I am not really a fan of the buffalo wing, but these are amazing! We got a party tray for a superbowl party and they were the hit of the night. The leftovers were even amazing warmed in the oven a few days later. I've also had burgers, which aren't much to write home about. But everuthing  was amazing!. The restaurant was clean.. People are almost always friendly and really enjoy their jobs. It's fun to go, and even more fun to eat!

Huge football Sunday and my place was chosen as the place to watch the games. My friends can eat like football players themselves. Atomic Wings in Brooklyn made the whole process from order to delivery so easy. You can order right online and the process was ideal with all the wings options Style, Size and Sauce right there for you. My guys always are specific in what they enjoy, so I ordered a detail variety of wings and it all came as ordered. We are just enjoying them now, but so far the boys are loving them. The only negative is that I now have to host the Super Bowl Party. Once you provide the incredible food, they will never want to go elsewhere. Atomic Wings in Brooklyn will be getting a sizable order from me in two weeks. If you want delicious wings and an easy to order/delivery process chose Atomic Wings in Brooklyn. You can thank me later. Enjoy !
